    {
        "content": "<p>You can use <code>module.declare_data_in_func</code> passing in both the id returned from <code>declare_data</code> and a mutable reference to the <code>Function</code> you are creating. This method then returns a <code>GlobalValue</code> you can pass to the <code>global_value</code> instruction to get a <code>Value</code> representing the address of the data object.</p>",
        "id": 452429254,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1721332767
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>mind.blown()</code> Do you have an example?</p>\n<p>Do i need to tell it to dereference that <code>Value</code> that is returned?</p>",
        "id": 452440561,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Clark",
        "timestamp": 1721336638
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you want to get the value stored in the global variable you did need to load from the address returned by <code>global_value</code> and if you want to change the value you need to use <code>store</code>.</p>",
        "id": 452586431,
